1
00:01:09,820 --> 00:01:13,500
=Inherently Kind=

2
00:01:14,780 --> 00:01:17,700
=Episode 7=
(Who Am I?)

3
00:01:18,959 --> 00:01:20,000
After all these years,

4
00:01:20,560 --> 00:01:21,959
I did not know her well.

5
00:01:23,680 --> 00:01:24,560
It looks like

6
00:01:25,120 --> 00:01:26,680
she really likes jewelry.

7
00:01:29,040 --> 00:01:29,680
(Happy birthday.)

8
00:01:30,280 --> 00:01:30,840
(Thank you.)

9
00:01:31,120 --> 00:01:32,920
But why did she act so indifferent

10
00:01:33,760 --> 00:01:35,519
at the birthday banquet?

11
00:01:47,079 --> 00:01:49,239
This does not look like real jade.

12
00:01:52,100 --> 00:01:54,239
(Yacang Tea House)

13
00:01:54,239 --> 00:01:55,920
Yacang Tea House?

14
00:01:57,760 --> 00:01:59,920
You're always
fiddling with your jewelry.

15
00:02:00,040 --> 00:02:01,560
And you don't care about the family?

16
00:02:02,599 --> 00:02:03,120
Mom.

17
00:02:03,840 --> 00:02:05,680
Why are you so angry?

18
00:02:06,319 --> 00:02:07,680
Just tell me what you want.

19
00:02:08,360 --> 00:02:10,400
Our family doesn't support
useless people.

20
00:02:10,759 --> 00:02:12,960
Today, you get this closet cleaned.

21
00:02:13,159 --> 00:02:15,159
And clean all the jewelry.

22
00:02:16,319 --> 00:02:16,800
Sure.

23
00:02:17,319 --> 00:02:18,599
I was also planning to tidy up here.

24
00:02:20,159 --> 00:02:21,120
At least you know your place!

25
00:02:21,639 --> 00:02:22,439
Stay and supervise her!

26
00:02:22,520 --> 00:02:23,919
No food until everything is clean!

27
00:02:30,479 --> 00:02:30,919
Madam Gu.

28
00:02:31,000 --> 00:02:31,879
You are so slow.

29
00:02:32,000 --> 00:02:33,039
Do you even know how to do this?

30
00:02:35,000 --> 00:02:36,719
If not this way, then how?

31
00:02:37,199 --> 00:02:37,879
You have to...

32
00:02:41,000 --> 00:02:42,639
How could you break
such an expensive jade?

33
00:02:43,080 --> 00:02:44,560
You set me up on purpose!

34
00:02:44,840 --> 00:02:46,080
We are even now, aren't we?

35
00:02:47,319 --> 00:02:48,120
What do you mean?

36
00:02:49,800 --> 00:02:52,240
You were the one who pushed me
last night, weren't you?

37
00:02:54,240 --> 00:02:55,319
The scent on you

38
00:02:55,960 --> 00:02:56,960
is exactly the same as hers.

39
00:02:58,520 --> 00:02:59,919
Was last lesson not enough for you?

40
00:03:00,840 --> 00:03:01,560
Madam Gu.

41
00:03:01,680 --> 00:03:02,159
I...

42
00:03:02,520 --> 00:03:03,800
I did not mean to.

43
00:03:04,000 --> 00:03:05,400
You can continue working for him.

44
00:03:06,520 --> 00:03:06,960
Or...

45
00:03:09,400 --> 00:03:10,400
Be smarter.

46
00:03:19,759 --> 00:03:20,439
Miss Gu,

47
00:03:21,039 --> 00:03:22,240
for a counterfeit like this,

48
00:03:22,439 --> 00:03:24,000
is it worth your time
coming here in person?

49
00:03:24,879 --> 00:03:25,599
Didn't you sell

50
00:03:25,840 --> 00:03:27,680
the genuine piece to me six months ago?

51
00:03:28,280 --> 00:03:30,159
What do you mean now?

52
00:03:31,919 --> 00:03:33,039
To be honest,

53
00:03:33,639 --> 00:03:36,120
I had a car accident some time ago.

54
00:03:36,719 --> 00:03:37,719
And I have forgotten many things.

55
00:03:38,439 --> 00:03:39,599
I can't remember

56
00:03:39,800 --> 00:03:40,599
any of the jewelry before,

57
00:03:40,719 --> 00:03:41,680
so I wonder

58
00:03:41,840 --> 00:03:44,240
if you could send me
our transaction records

59
00:03:44,400 --> 00:03:45,120
for me to take a look.

60
00:03:46,599 --> 00:03:47,960
Sure, I will send them to you.

61
00:03:51,080 --> 00:03:53,280
From last December to this May,

62
00:03:53,639 --> 00:03:55,800
(Jewelry List, Earrings and Necklaces)
you sold seven pieces of jewelry to me.

63
00:03:56,080 --> 00:03:56,680
They are all here.

64
00:03:57,039 --> 00:03:57,759
(Just as I thought.)

65
00:03:58,360 --> 00:04:00,240
(This matches Gu Qingmei's diary.)

66
00:04:01,080 --> 00:04:02,960
(Madam Gu, please have mercy on me!)

67
00:04:03,560 --> 00:04:04,599
(These are all fakes!)

68
00:04:04,759 --> 00:04:05,639
(They are worthless!)

69
00:04:05,960 --> 00:04:06,719
(How do you know?)

70
00:04:06,879 --> 00:04:08,360
(Last month, I overheard you)

71
00:04:08,560 --> 00:04:10,840
(arguing with He Jinchuan by the pool.)

72
00:04:11,159 --> 00:04:11,639
(You said)

73
00:04:11,800 --> 00:04:13,919
(you were going to sell all the jewelry)

74
00:04:14,280 --> 00:04:16,079
(and you still hadn't raised
the 30 million for him.)

75
00:04:16,480 --> 00:04:18,600
(You were worried that people would
find out about the counterfeits.)

76
00:04:19,279 --> 00:04:20,399
(He Jinchuan?)

77
00:04:21,759 --> 00:04:22,360
(You mean)

78
00:04:22,480 --> 00:04:23,879
(I sold all the jewelry)

79
00:04:24,000 --> 00:04:25,319
(and gave the money to He Jinchuan?)

80
00:04:25,720 --> 00:04:26,480
(Yes.)

81
00:04:26,759 --> 00:04:30,240
(It was about some investment project.)

82
00:04:31,360 --> 00:04:33,040
(Gu Qingmei, you fool!)

83
00:04:33,879 --> 00:04:34,439
(All that money)

84
00:04:34,480 --> 00:04:36,399
(was swindled by Jinchuan!)

85
00:04:37,519 --> 00:04:40,040
(Transaction Date)
(Two pieces sold on May 20th.)

86
00:04:41,160 --> 00:04:42,199
These two auction pieces,

87
00:04:42,319 --> 00:04:43,360
you bought them on that same day?

88
00:04:43,959 --> 00:04:44,560
Yes.

89
00:04:45,000 --> 00:04:45,959
Right after the auction,

90
00:04:46,120 --> 00:04:47,199
you rushed to close the deal

91
00:04:47,600 --> 00:04:48,759
and demanded cash payment.

92
00:04:49,720 --> 00:04:51,399
(I was already in hospital that time.)

93
00:04:52,439 --> 00:04:53,839
(After Gu Qingmei sold the jewelry,)

94
00:04:54,399 --> 00:04:55,399
(where did she go?)

95
00:04:57,319 --> 00:04:57,920
Miss Gu,

96
00:04:59,680 --> 00:05:01,560
are you okay?

97
00:05:02,759 --> 00:05:03,319
I'm fine.

98
00:05:04,199 --> 00:05:06,079
I just confirmed something.

99
00:05:12,600 --> 00:05:13,199
Mrs. He.

100
00:05:15,079 --> 00:05:15,560
Mrs. He.

101
00:05:16,120 --> 00:05:16,879
I am so sorry.

102
00:05:17,839 --> 00:05:19,600
The camera for the charity auction night

103
00:05:19,639 --> 00:05:20,399
all malfunctioned.

104
00:05:20,759 --> 00:05:21,399
So...

105
00:05:21,920 --> 00:05:23,480
All the data was lost.

106
00:05:23,639 --> 00:05:24,360
What a coincidence!

107
00:05:24,879 --> 00:05:27,000
The footage on that day was lost.

108
00:05:27,920 --> 00:05:29,800
Was it deleted on purpose?

109
00:05:30,319 --> 00:05:31,000
Well...

110
00:05:31,879 --> 00:05:33,560
So much time has passed.

111
00:05:34,000 --> 00:05:34,839
As for that,

112
00:05:35,120 --> 00:05:36,279
we really cannot confirm.

113
00:05:46,680 --> 00:05:49,040
(Who was behind this?)

114
00:05:50,839 --> 00:05:52,720
(Why did I become a substitute for her?)

115
00:05:56,560 --> 00:05:57,519
(And who am I?)

116
00:06:06,040 --> 00:06:06,920
(Mrs. He,)

117
00:06:07,519 --> 00:06:09,560
(have trouble finding your seat?)

118
00:06:10,160 --> 00:06:10,959
(Mrs. He?)

119
00:06:12,560 --> 00:06:13,120
(Yes.)

120
00:06:16,079 --> 00:06:16,800
Mrs. He?

121
00:06:20,480 --> 00:06:21,199
We meet again.

122
00:06:21,759 --> 00:06:23,319
You did a great job at the last banquet.

123
00:06:23,680 --> 00:06:24,279
Not at all.

124
00:06:24,480 --> 00:06:25,680
I am very happy to serve you.

125
00:06:27,839 --> 00:06:28,839
Why do I get the feeling

126
00:06:29,360 --> 00:06:30,720
that you seem afraid of me?

127
00:06:31,319 --> 00:06:33,000
Was I not polite last time?

128
00:06:33,199 --> 00:06:33,920
No, no.

129
00:06:34,439 --> 00:06:37,399
You were a little strange last time.

130
00:06:37,720 --> 00:06:38,279
Strange?

131
00:06:39,240 --> 00:06:40,120
What's so strange about me?

132
00:06:40,680 --> 00:06:42,040
The first time you came in,

133
00:06:42,199 --> 00:06:43,199
you looked worried.

134
00:06:43,560 --> 00:06:44,360
Then when you came in again,

135
00:06:44,600 --> 00:06:45,879
you were all smiles.

136
00:06:46,120 --> 00:06:48,519
I thought your emotional control

137
00:06:48,560 --> 00:06:49,279
was quite impressive.

138
00:06:49,920 --> 00:06:50,639
The second time...

139
00:06:52,040 --> 00:06:53,240
I came in twice?

140
00:06:53,399 --> 00:06:53,959
Yes.

141
00:06:54,639 --> 00:06:55,519
Do you not remember?

142
00:07:10,439 --> 00:07:10,920
Stop right there!

143
00:07:13,639 --> 00:07:14,199
Why are you running?

144
00:07:15,879 --> 00:07:16,480
I am sorry.

145
00:07:17,000 --> 00:07:18,399
I should not have slandered
Meiyan International.

146
00:07:19,240 --> 00:07:20,600
The information in the USB drive

147
00:07:20,720 --> 00:07:21,360
was fake.

148
00:07:22,120 --> 00:07:23,639
I made it all up.

149
00:07:24,879 --> 00:07:25,720
USB drive?

150
00:07:26,879 --> 00:07:27,879
Why would you make up that information?

151
00:07:29,360 --> 00:07:30,560
I was forced to.

152
00:07:31,600 --> 00:07:33,600
I worked in quality control
at Meiyan International for ten years.

153
00:07:34,240 --> 00:07:35,720
Then I was suddenly fired last year.

154
00:07:36,879 --> 00:07:38,680
I never received any compensation.

155
00:07:39,160 --> 00:07:40,120
I was just pissed,

156
00:07:40,680 --> 00:07:42,319
so I wanted to find something
to use against them.

157
00:07:44,680 --> 00:07:45,800
Since it is fabricated,

158
00:07:45,839 --> 00:07:46,720
then why did you give it to me?

159
00:07:49,279 --> 00:07:51,240
I posted complaints
about Meiyan International online

160
00:07:51,680 --> 00:07:53,199
and got to know
a journalist named Su Su.

161
00:07:53,720 --> 00:07:54,920
I was planning to cause a scene

162
00:07:55,040 --> 00:07:55,800
at the auction.

163
00:07:56,160 --> 00:07:57,759
But then I was hunted.

164
00:07:58,639 --> 00:07:59,600
I was also scared,

165
00:08:00,920 --> 00:08:02,120
so I gave you the USB drive.

166
00:08:03,319 --> 00:08:04,920
Who knew you'd turn out to be Mrs. He?

167
00:08:05,480 --> 00:08:06,879
The one behind Meiyan International

168
00:08:07,279 --> 00:08:08,399
turned out to be your husband.

169
00:08:09,040 --> 00:08:10,800
(The one behind Meiyan International)

170
00:08:11,399 --> 00:08:12,560
(turns out to be He Jinchen.)

171
00:08:14,240 --> 00:08:15,680
Mrs. He, I was wrong!

172
00:08:15,839 --> 00:08:16,879
Please forgive me!

173
00:08:17,040 --> 00:08:17,959
Give me a chance!

174
00:08:21,279 --> 00:08:22,959
I lost the USB drive last time.

175
00:08:23,480 --> 00:08:24,160
I need another copy.

176
00:08:25,720 --> 00:08:26,319
The USB drive...

177
00:08:26,879 --> 00:08:27,360
Alright.

178
00:08:27,639 --> 00:08:29,079
The USB drive is on my computer.

179
00:08:29,839 --> 00:08:30,800
I will take you to get it.

180
00:08:31,240 --> 00:08:31,680
Lead the way.

181
00:08:34,639 --> 00:08:36,360
Continue searching for Gu Qingmei.

182
00:08:37,720 --> 00:08:38,960
Bring her back alive,

183
00:08:39,679 --> 00:08:41,159
or bring me a body.

184
00:08:42,000 --> 00:08:42,480
Boss.

185
00:08:42,879 --> 00:08:44,080
what about the one in the He family?

186
00:08:44,759 --> 00:08:47,480
Leave her as Miss Gu for now.

187
00:08:48,279 --> 00:08:49,159
Our source said

188
00:08:49,600 --> 00:08:50,679
she went to see Tian Gang again.

189
00:08:51,200 --> 00:08:52,000
But we don't know

190
00:08:52,120 --> 00:08:53,799
whether she had the USB drive.

191
00:08:54,399 --> 00:08:55,519
Tian Gang.

192
00:08:57,159 --> 00:08:58,360
Go and take care of him!

193
00:08:59,960 --> 00:09:00,960
As for that woman,

194
00:09:02,039 --> 00:09:03,440
leave her alive.

195
00:09:04,519 --> 00:09:08,240
I want her to be Gu Qingmei for now.

196
00:09:13,440 --> 00:09:14,039
What are you looking at?

197
00:09:58,039 --> 00:09:59,639
(These two car accidents)

198
00:10:00,000 --> 00:10:00,960
(appear to be no accidents.)

199
00:10:02,200 --> 00:10:02,960
(What's the secret)

200
00:10:03,080 --> 00:10:04,240
(in that USB drive)

201
00:10:05,159 --> 00:10:07,679
(that keeps them coming after me?)

202
00:10:14,960 --> 00:10:15,919
I have handled him.

203
00:10:16,320 --> 00:10:16,879
Don't worry.

204
00:10:18,480 --> 00:10:19,039
Thank you.

205
00:10:22,240 --> 00:10:23,000
By the way,

206
00:10:23,159 --> 00:10:24,240
did you offend someone?

207
00:10:24,879 --> 00:10:26,399
Why are people always after you?

208
00:10:27,279 --> 00:10:28,399
I was just about to say.

209
00:10:28,840 --> 00:10:30,399
Whenever something happens to me,

210
00:10:31,639 --> 00:10:32,320
you are always there.

211
00:10:32,720 --> 00:10:34,480
Did you arrange these rescues
to play the hero?

212
00:10:41,799 --> 00:10:42,519
You are injured!

213
00:10:45,080 --> 00:10:46,000
Are you not injured too?

214
00:10:51,519 --> 00:10:52,000
Qingmei!

215
00:10:54,080 --> 00:10:54,720
Come with me!

216
00:10:57,519 --> 00:10:58,320
Didn't you see she is injured?

217
00:11:00,399 --> 00:11:01,279
My wife

218
00:11:01,679 --> 00:11:03,320
does not need your concern, Mr. Mu.

219
00:11:06,559 --> 00:11:07,399
Aren't we going home?

220
00:11:07,799 --> 00:11:08,320
Let's go.

221
00:11:18,639 --> 00:11:19,080
Hello.

222
00:11:20,840 --> 00:11:21,360
Check that car

223
00:11:21,919 --> 00:11:22,919
and see if it has any connection

224
00:11:23,159 --> 00:11:24,279
to the previous one.

225
00:11:41,720 --> 00:11:42,279
Recently,

226
00:11:42,720 --> 00:11:44,519
you have been getting a little close
to Mu Shaoze.

227
00:11:45,720 --> 00:11:46,840
We are just business partners.

228
00:11:47,000 --> 00:11:48,240
Business partners?

229
00:11:48,679 --> 00:11:50,320
Do you need to be that close?

230
00:11:50,519 --> 00:11:52,159
He was injured saving me.

231
00:11:52,399 --> 00:11:53,440
What's wrong with me checking on him?

232
00:11:53,960 --> 00:11:54,600
Besides,

233
00:11:54,919 --> 00:11:55,720
I almost lost my life.

234
00:11:55,799 --> 00:11:56,759
As my husband,

235
00:11:56,840 --> 00:11:57,720
did you even care about me once?

236
00:11:58,960 --> 00:12:00,279
Aren't you safe now?

237
00:12:00,440 --> 00:12:01,120
If something really happened...

238
00:12:01,159 --> 00:12:01,720
So I have to actually be in trouble

239
00:12:01,759 --> 00:12:02,720
before you come mourn me?

240
00:12:03,360 --> 00:12:05,039
Or are you unhappy that I did not die?

241
00:12:05,480 --> 00:12:07,360
Why are you so sharp-tongued now?

242
00:12:07,720 --> 00:12:09,360
You used to be so gentle and kind.

243
00:12:10,200 --> 00:12:10,879
Kind?

244
00:12:12,000 --> 00:12:13,000
If swallowing your pride

245
00:12:13,039 --> 00:12:14,480
and never talking back is being kind,

246
00:12:14,559 --> 00:12:15,720
then I have had enough!

247
00:12:16,519 --> 00:12:18,120
I just wanted to remind you

248
00:12:18,279 --> 00:12:19,320
not to get too close.

249
00:12:19,480 --> 00:12:21,919
Are you jealous?

250
00:12:22,480 --> 00:12:23,320
Mu Shaoze

251
00:12:23,600 --> 00:12:25,080
is Jinxi's fiancé.

252
00:12:25,240 --> 00:12:26,879
You'd better know your place!

253
00:12:27,720 --> 00:12:28,279
Why?

254
00:12:29,039 --> 00:12:30,159
Afraid I might cheat on you?

255
00:12:31,039 --> 00:12:32,200
He is not that simple.

256
00:12:32,720 --> 00:12:33,840
Maybe he is only getting close to you

257
00:12:34,159 --> 00:12:35,799
because he's after Gu Corporation.

258
00:12:36,200 --> 00:12:36,759
And what about you?

259
00:12:38,320 --> 00:12:39,960
You're not interested in
Gu Corporation at all?

260
00:12:41,679 --> 00:12:42,679
We're married.

261
00:12:43,200 --> 00:12:44,399
Of course I'm on your side.

262
00:12:45,840 --> 00:12:46,279
Sure.

263
00:12:47,480 --> 00:12:48,840
Then I'll be counting on you, dear.

264
00:13:09,340 --> 00:13:14,100
♪Time stole the proof of our love♪

265
00:13:14,100 --> 00:13:18,940
♪Hidden in the moonlight,
lost in the clouds♪

266
00:13:18,940 --> 00:13:23,500
♪Tangled glances and love fall together♪

267
00:13:23,500 --> 00:13:28,420
♪Into a spiral of thoughts,
memories rewinding♪

268
00:13:28,420 --> 00:13:32,220
♪Feelings both strange and familiar♪

269
00:13:32,220 --> 00:13:37,020
♪I just know you're
where my heart belongs♪

270
00:13:37,020 --> 00:13:39,860
♪Can't remember
when this flutter started♪

271
00:13:39,860 --> 00:13:42,540
♪Or how it's supposed to end♪

272
00:13:42,900 --> 00:13:48,460
♪Goodbye to the world rushing in♪

273
00:13:48,860 --> 00:13:55,660
♪Let me hide in your eyes
and never leave♪

274
00:13:55,940 --> 00:14:00,620
♪Feel the rhythm of your heartbeat♪

275
00:14:00,780 --> 00:14:07,580
♪Every tomorrow seems worth the wait♪

276
00:14:07,900 --> 00:14:14,700
♪Let me fill the emptiness of a century♪

277
00:14:14,900 --> 00:14:19,380
♪As the wind brushes past your hem♪

278
00:14:19,380 --> 00:14:22,740
♪All my hidden feelings come undone♪

279
00:14:22,740 --> 00:14:29,660
♪Right as I confess my love♪
